---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Midnight Society Support — Ergo Sum"
  description="Get help with Midnight Society — a local multiplayer social deduction game."
>
  <section class="py-24 sm:py-32" data-reveal>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">Midnight Society</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl leading-relaxed text-apple-muted">
        A local multiplayer social deduction game for 3–10 players. No internet required — just
        gather your friends on the same WiFi network and start playing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16" data-reveal>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">System Requirements</h2>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-lg text-apple-muted">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="font-medium text-apple-text">iOS</span> — 26.0 or later
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="font-medium text-apple-text">Devices</span> — iPhone and iPad (universal)
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="font-medium text-apple-text">Network</span> — Local WiFi only. No internet connection required.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16" data-reveal>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Getting Started</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-apple-muted">
        <p>
          Make sure all players are connected to the same WiFi network. One person creates a game
          as the host, and everyone else joins from the lobby screen. Once everyone's in, the host
          starts the game.
        </p>
        <p>
          A typical game lasts about 10–20 minutes and runs through several phases: role reveal,
          night, discussion, voting, and results.
        </p>
        <p>
          The discussion phase has a 5-minute timer that the host can pause if needed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16" data-reveal>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Multiplayer &amp; Connectivity</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">How does multiplayer work?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-apple-muted">
            Midnight Society uses local WiFi (Bonjour/mDNS) to connect players. The host advertises
            the game, and nearby players on the same network can browse and join. There's a
            30-second window to accept invitations.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Do I need Bluetooth?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-apple-muted">
            No. The game uses WiFi only. All players must be on the same local network.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">I can't find other players.</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-apple-muted">
            Make sure everyone is on the same WiFi network, and that each player has granted the
            app Local Network permission in Settings → Privacy & Security → Local Network.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Someone disconnected mid-game.</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-apple-muted">
            Disconnected players are tracked by the game and can rejoin. The host will receive an
            updated game state when they reconnect.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16" data-reveal>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">In-App Purchases</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-lg text-apple-muted">
        <p>
          Midnight Society includes one optional purchase:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-2">
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-apple-text">Doomsayer Role</span> — $2.99 (one-time purchase). Unlocks an additional role for your games.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This is a non-consumable purchase tied to your Apple ID. If you've already purchased it,
          you can restore it from the in-app purchase screen via Restore Purchases.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16" data-reveal>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Data &amp; Privacy</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-lg text-apple-muted">
        <p>
          Midnight Society stores all data locally on your device. There are no accounts, no cloud
          sync, no analytics, and no tracking.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-2">
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-apple-text">Profile data</span> — Your name, avatar
            symbol, avatar color, and optional photo are stored on-device only.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-apple-text">Purchase history</span> — Cached locally
            for convenience. The App Store is the source of truth.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-apple-text">Deleting your data</span> — You can delete
            your profile from within the app. To remove all app data completely, delete and
            reinstall the app.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          For full details, see our <a href="/legal/privacy" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">privacy policy</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 sm:py-32" data-reveal>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Still need help?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-apple-muted">
        Email us at
        <a href="mailto:support@ergosum.studio" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">support@ergosum.studio</a>
        and we'll get back to you as soon as we can.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
